cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with deep learning algorithms and their performance on imbalanced datasets, which is a common problem in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a new loss function and a training schedule, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
